{"type":"message","id":"9b296649","parentId":"90511433","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:23:36.453Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y2yla9ldl7ya_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142214\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. I just completed a CFI Compression Experiment with significant findings\r\n2. The next action is clear: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\" - this is the top priority\r\n3. The formula to test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n4. I need to run 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe observation is that I have a concrete next experiment defined from the CFI synthesis work. The action is to implement and run this experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me implement this experiment by:\r\n1. Creating a script that calculates the hybrid score\r\n2. Running it on the pulse data\r\n3. Comparing against the binary thresholds from the previous experiment\r\n\r\nI should create a new analysis script that implements Strategy C.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis documented that the constant-format problem (freq≈160, CFI=1) requires a hybrid scoring approach. Strategy C's formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) is ready to be tested against the binary thresholds from the prior experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment script to compare against binary threshold results (precision 0.5653, recall 0.0724).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Compare against binary thresholds from prior experiment\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport os\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\npulses_dir = \"pulses\"\r\npulse_files = sorted([f for f in os.listdir(pulses_dir) if f.startswith(\"pulse_\") and f.endswith(\".md\")])\r\ntrain_size = int(len(pulse_files) * 0.8)\r\ntrain_files = pulse_files[:train_size]\r\ntest_files = pulse_files[train_size:]\r\n\r\n# Build token frequency and CFI from training set\r\nfreq = defaultdict(int)\r\ntoken_contexts = defaultdict(set)  # token -> set of files it appears in\r\nall_tokens_per_file = defaultdict(list)\r\n\r\nfor pf in train_files:\r\n    with open(os.path.join(pulses_dir, pf)) as f:\r\n        tokens = f.read().split()\r\n    all_tokens_per_file[pf] = tokens\r\n    for t in tokens:\r\n        freq[t] += 1\r\n        token_contexts[t].add(pf)\r\n\r\ntotal_files = len(train_files)\r\ncfi = {}\r\nfor t, contexts in token_contexts.items():\r\n    cfi[t] = len(contexts) / total_files\r\n\r\n# Calculate hybrid scores\r\ndef hybrid_score(token):\r\n    freq_val = freq.get(token, 0)\r\n    cfi_val = cfi.get(token, 0)\r\n    if freq_val == 0:\r\n        return 0\r\n    freq_factor = min(1.0, freq_val / 120)\r\n    return cfi_val * freq_factor\r\n\r\n# Get test set ground truth tokens\r\ntest_tokens = set()\r\nfor pf in test_files:\r\n    with open(os.path.join(pulses_dir, pf)) as f:\r\n        test_tokens.update(f.read().split())\r\n\r\n# Calculate scores for all tokens\r\ntoken_scores = [(t, hybrid_score(t), freq[t], cfi[t]) for t in freq]\r\ntoken_scores.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])  # Sort by hybrid score descending\r\n\r\n# Find optimal threshold via F1\r\nbest_f1, best_thresh, best_prec, best_rec = 0, 0, 0, 0\r\nfor thresh in [0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3, 0.35, 0.4, 0.45, 0.5]:\r\n    predicted = set(t for t, s, f, c in token_scores if s >= thresh)\r\n    tp = len(predicted & test_tokens)\r\n    prec = tp / len(predicted) if predicted else 0\r\n    rec = tp / len(test_tokens) if test_tokens else 0\r\n    f1 = 2 * prec * rec / (prec + rec) if (prec + rec) > 0 else 0\r\n    if f1 > best_f1:\r\n        best_f1, best_thresh, best_prec, best_rec = f1, thresh, prec, rec\r\n\r\n# Compare with binary thresholds from prior experiment\r\nprior_prec, prior_rec = 0.5653, 0.0724\r\n\r\nresults = f\"\"\"# Strategy C Results: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring\r\n\r\n## Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Setup\r\n- Training set: {len(train_files)} files\r\n- Test set: {len(test_files)} files\r\n- Total unique tokens: {len(freq)}\r\n\r\n## Optimal Threshold Analysis\r\nBest threshold: {best_thresh:.2f}\r\n- Precision: {best_prec:.4f}\r\n- Recall: {best_rec:.4f}\r\n- F1: {best_f1:.4f}\r\n\r\n## Comparison with Binary Thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7, freq < 60)\r\n- Prior: Precision={prior_prec:.4f}, Recall={prior_rec:.4f}\r\n- Strategy C: Precision={best_prec:.4f}, Recall={best_rec:.4f}\r\n- Precision delta: {best_prec - prior_prec:+.4f}\r\n- Recall delta: {best_rec - prior_rec:+.4f}\r\n\r\n## Top 20\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:22:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376616449}}
