{"type":"message","id":"672402e9","parentId":"158ad432","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:23:44.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_t3f2qsb61ow4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142315\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: and (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent progress:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The CFI Compression Experiment was just completed with key findings\r\n3. The next pending experiment is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from the CFI experiment is:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Need to test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nI should run this experiment. Looking at the existing code and data:\r\n- There's a `research/` directory with previous experiment files\r\n- The pulse script exists and works\r\n\r\nLet me check what's available for running the experiment. The key file for the CFI experiment was `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Create or update a file that implements the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Run it on the pulse data\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md, it likely has the experimental setup. I should create a new experiment file that implements the hybrid scoring and runs it.\r\n\r\nLet me create a new file `research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md` with the experiment plan and then implement the analysis.\r\n\r\nActually, let me look at what files exist in the research directory. The previous experiment files were:\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a new experiment file that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Computes the hybrid score = CFI × min(1, freq/120)\r\n3. Compares against the binary threshold results\r\n4. Determines if it better separates constant-format from research tokens\r\n\r\nLet me write a concrete action to advance this goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment revealed the \"constant format problem\" - tokens like \"for next instantiation\" with freq=160 and CFI=1.00 are pure metaprogramming artifacts. The hybrid formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` should separate these from true research tokens like \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96). This experiment is ready to run.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and execute the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment to test whether the multiplicative formula distinguishes constant-format tokens (high freq, high CFI) from research trajectory tokens (moderate freq, high CFI).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Objective:** Test if score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) separates constant-format from research tokens\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- Constant-format tokens: freq≈160, CFI≈1.00 → score = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\r\n- Research tokens: freq≈136, CFI≈0.96 → score = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96\r\n- **Problem:** Both score near 1.0. Need to reconsider.\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/120)^0.5\r\n- \"for next instantiation\": 1.0 × (160/120)^0.5 = 1.0 × 1.155 = **1.155**\r\n- \"Phase 1\": 0.96 × (136/120)^0.5 = 0.96 × 1.065 = **1.022**\r\n\r\nStill too close. Need frequency PENALTY for constant tokens.\r\n\r\n## Final Formula (to test)\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × clamp(1 - (freq(T) - 100)/200, 0.1, 1.0)\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160): 1.0 × clamp(1 - 60/200, 0.1, 1.0) = 1.0 × 0.7 = **0.70**\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136): 0.96 × clamp(1 - 36/200, 0.1, 1.0) = 0.96 × 0.82 = **0.79**\r\n- \"for\" (freq=200): 0.95 × clamp(1 - 100/200, 0.1, 1.0) = 0.95 × 0.5 = **0.475**\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n1. Extract all tokens from pulse corpus\r\n2. Compute CFI(T) and freq(T) for each token\r\n3. Apply three scoring methods:\r\n   - **Binary:** CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - **Linear Penalty:** CFI × clamp(1 - (freq-100)/200, 0.1, 1.0)\r\n   - **Sqrt Dampened:** CFI × min(1, sqrt(freq/120))\r\n4. Compare precision/recall for identifying \"true research tokens\" (manually labeled)\r\n5. Determine which method best separates constant-format from causal tokens\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:23:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376624986}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a33acfe","parentId":"672402e9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:23:51.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the pulse results concisely.","thinkingSignature":"7100f144cd1879104e1afbe34c2e4f9bea5ab2242676729b0b086271a4a77189"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 14:23**\n\n**What happened:**\n- Git commit `7fb18ce` — 6 files changed, +193/-105 lines\n- Proposed mutation: `research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md` — a new experiment to test whether a frequency-penalized hybrid scoring formula (`CFI × clamp(1 - (freq-100)/200, 0.1, 1.0)`) can distinguish constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0 → score 0.70) from research tokens (freq≈136, CFI=0.96 → score 0.79)\n- Previous mutation (Strategy C from prior pulse) was **rejected** and moved to `/rejected/`\n\n**Core insight driving this:** The pure CFI×Freq multiplier fails because both constant-format and research tokens score near 1.0. The frequency penalty approach creates meaningful separation (0.70 vs 0.79), though the margin remains tight."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3524,"output":241,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15902,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774376624988}}
